      <p>
        <!-- TODO: Update the text with your own -->
     The more that you know about the clothes that your buying, the better. Usually when looking and shopping for clothes, we just look for what looks best on us. While we're not trying to change that, we want to change the clothing that you buy on a much deeper level.
  Looking at the material your clothing is made from is a huge starting point. Natural fabrics like organic cotton and linen (made from plants) and Tencel (made from sustainable wood pulp) are the best for the environment. Asking where your clothing came from is very important
        as well. If it's from Bangledesh, India, Indonesia, China, etc. it was probably made under unethical conditions while they were being paid less than a livable wage. Clothing made in countries where your from, tend to have better working conditions. 
